Zero-Trust GitHub Actions to AWS Lambda Deployment
This project demonstrates how to create a secure, zero-trust CI/CD pipeline. It deploys a serverless AWS Lambda function using GitHub Actions without any long-lived static secrets like AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID.

The pipeline achieves this by configuring a trust relationship between GitHub and AWS using OpenID Connect (OIDC).

.
├── .github/
│   └── workflows/
│       └── ci.yml        
├── infra/
│   └── main.tf           
├── src/
│   └── index.js          
├── .gitignore             
└── Steps_followed    

Step 1:Gather your AWS/GitHub accounts and install the necessary command-line tools.

Step 2:Define the required AWS OIDC and IAM role infrastructure using Terraform code.

Step 3:Write the simple "Hello World" code for the AWS Lambda function.

Step 4:Create the GitHub Actions workflow YAML file to define the CI/CD pipeline.

Step 5:Push the code to your GitHub repository to automatically trigger the deployment process.
